pr_review_comment_body:
Since this adds support for the many available options added to the README, it might be time to have a helper function that pulls configuration values from the environment, where any configurable value could be set by an environment variable. This would not only include airbrake credentials (e.g. api key) but also values that are sent in the payloads when notifying of an errors (e.g. environment, app_version, user_email). 

Something like

```python
def airbrake_environment_vars():
    return {k.lstrip('AIRBRAKE_').lower(): v
            for k, v in os.environ.items()
            if k.upper().startswith('AIRBRAKE_')}

It also seems reasonable to go forward with this PR, perhaps you could add this to the roadmap.

@kmuehlbauer 
Thanks for clarifying the problem. I see the issue now. You have a newest version of the Rainbow file. I would love to have this information in my own files! :).
I think the best approach is to have a chain of elif:

if (len(ray_info) == 1):
    treatment of case with angle_start only
elif (len(ray_info)==2):
    treatnment of case with angle_start and angle_stop
else:
   treatment of case with all the additional information

I assume that the ray information is given in an specified order so we can keep using indices to access the information in ray_info anyway.

Does this approach make sense to you?

I had a fast glance and didn't found anything.

